tspan.tspan: Metric Temporal Logic (MTL) is a formalization tool

text.tspan: that incorporates time-bound statements using atomic propositions,
Boolean operators, and temporal operators. Key temporal operators
include G (globally), X (next), F (eventually), O (once), and S (since),
which can be used with specific time intervals [lb, ub]. Additionally,
Boolean operators ¬ (not), ∧ (and), ∨ (or), and the implication
operator a =⇒ b (defined as ¬a ∨ b) are essential components.
